WEBVTT

00:03.237 --> 00:05.339
[ Squeaks ]

00:05.373 --> 00:07.408
[ Laughing ]

00:10.878 --> 00:13.747
[ Screeches ]

00:13.781 --> 00:14.882
♪ Adventure time

00:14.915 --> 00:16.217
♪ Come on, grab your friends

00:16.250 --> 00:18.986
♪ We'll go to
very distant lands ♪

00:19.019 --> 00:21.555
♪ With Jake the dog
and Finn the human ♪

00:21.589 --> 00:23.023
♪ And the fun will never end

00:23.057 --> 00:25.293
♪ It's adventure time

00:33.467 --> 00:34.668
Jake: [ Shouting ]
Finn?

00:34.702 --> 00:35.703
Finn: Yo.

00:35.736 --> 00:36.870
Oh, hey.

00:36.904 --> 00:39.573
Me and BMO are heading over
to the vuvuzela store

00:39.607 --> 00:40.674
in the music kingdom.

00:40.708 --> 00:42.009
You want to come with?

00:42.042 --> 00:44.011
I got to get
a new vuvuzela.

00:44.044 --> 00:46.046
Somebody keeps smashing
my old one.

00:46.080 --> 00:47.848
[ Blows raspberry ]

00:47.881 --> 00:49.083
[ BMO screams ]

00:49.117 --> 00:50.884
I can't bear this burden
any longer!

00:50.918 --> 00:52.120
It was me!

00:52.153 --> 00:53.921
I'm the vuvuzela smasher!

00:53.954 --> 00:55.856
BMO, how could you?

00:55.889 --> 00:58.226
Neptr: No, it was me!

00:58.259 --> 01:00.528
I'm the vuvuzela smasher.

01:00.561 --> 01:01.529
Neptr?!

01:01.562 --> 01:03.864
Finn: No, I'm
the vuvuzela smasher.

01:03.897 --> 01:05.299
All right, all right.

01:05.333 --> 01:07.034
Well, I'm still
getting one.

01:07.067 --> 01:08.136
You coming?

01:08.169 --> 01:09.603
Nah, me and Fin--

01:09.637 --> 01:11.205
Fern are supposed
to clean out

01:11.239 --> 01:12.373
the chicken coop today.

01:12.406 --> 01:14.208
And if anyone
tries to stop me,

01:14.242 --> 01:16.544
I'll slash
their flipping faces off.

01:16.577 --> 01:18.112
True, true.

01:18.146 --> 01:20.314
Okay, well,
I'll see you later then.

01:20.348 --> 01:21.815
Come on, BMO.

01:24.084 --> 01:25.319
BMO: Jake, I'm sorry!

01:25.353 --> 01:27.455
I really am the smasher!

01:27.488 --> 01:28.722
Jake: Ah, don't sweat it,
buddy.

01:28.756 --> 01:29.757
[ Laughs ]

01:29.790 --> 01:30.924
Holy cow!

01:30.958 --> 01:32.826
Fern, that was perfect!

01:32.860 --> 01:34.228
Hyup!

01:34.262 --> 01:36.096
You're getting new powers
like every day now.

01:36.130 --> 01:37.331
Let me see you do Jake --

01:37.365 --> 01:39.500
no, wait, Ice King!
Do Ice King!

01:39.533 --> 01:40.901
Ha, nah, man.

01:40.934 --> 01:42.170
[ Brrrb! ]

01:42.203 --> 01:43.904
Imitating uncool people
infects you

01:43.937 --> 01:45.606
with their loserishness.

01:45.639 --> 01:46.740
Oh.

01:46.774 --> 01:48.176
Yeah, that rings true.

01:48.209 --> 01:49.277
It's too bad
you didn't develop any

01:49.310 --> 01:50.578
coop-poop-scooping skills.

01:50.611 --> 01:52.780
That coop
is incredibly disgusting.

01:52.813 --> 01:55.749
Actually, about that,
I was thinking that,

01:55.783 --> 01:58.519
instead, maybe you and I
could explore

01:58.552 --> 02:00.421
some secret ruins I found.

02:00.454 --> 02:02.756
Secret ruins?!
Sweet!

02:02.790 --> 02:04.658
Maybe we can still catch up
with Jake and BMO!

02:04.692 --> 02:06.260
Or maybe Neptr
could come!

02:06.294 --> 02:08.462
Hey, Neptr, you want to go
on an adventure, buddy?!

02:08.496 --> 02:10.764
Neptr: Oh, my glob!
Hold on!

02:10.798 --> 02:12.633
Actually, I was thinking

02:12.666 --> 02:14.768
maybe just you and me
would go.

02:14.802 --> 02:17.004
Spend some quality time
together --

02:17.037 --> 02:19.173
Finn and Fern style.

02:19.207 --> 02:20.541
Yeah, okay.

02:20.574 --> 02:22.276
That actually even
sounds like something

02:22.310 --> 02:23.677
Jake would want us to do.

02:23.711 --> 02:26.980
[ Chuckles ]
Forget it, Neptr!

02:27.014 --> 02:28.148
♪ Dungeon surprise

02:28.182 --> 02:29.283
♪ Right before my eyes

02:29.317 --> 02:30.284
♪ What a surprise

02:30.318 --> 02:32.152
♪ The dungeon surprise

02:32.186 --> 02:34.522
Finn and Fern:
One, two, three -- shoot!

02:34.555 --> 02:35.389
Rock!

02:35.423 --> 02:37.625
One, two, three -- shoot!

02:37.658 --> 02:38.659
Scissors!

02:38.692 --> 02:39.460
[ Chuckles ]

02:39.493 --> 02:40.728
This is so weird.

02:40.761 --> 02:42.563
I can't tell if it's boring
or fun.

02:42.596 --> 02:44.665
Well, I can --
it's boring!

02:44.698 --> 02:47.335
I want the thrill
of victory!

02:47.368 --> 02:49.870
Who wants to be the same
all the time?

02:49.903 --> 02:51.239
Come on, man!

02:51.272 --> 02:52.706
You know you love it!

02:52.740 --> 02:54.074
Come on!

02:54.107 --> 02:55.976
One, two, three...

02:56.009 --> 02:57.044
Come on!

02:57.077 --> 02:58.646
[ Sighs ]

02:58.679 --> 03:00.914
Both:
One, two, three -- shoot.

03:00.948 --> 03:02.216
Rock.
Paper.

03:02.250 --> 03:03.984
What?!
Whoa!

03:04.017 --> 03:05.419
I won this time.

03:05.453 --> 03:08.155
What?
But that's not fair!

03:08.188 --> 03:09.189
[ Growls ]

03:09.223 --> 03:12.159
Why is nothing
ever fair?

03:12.192 --> 03:14.094
Hey, Fern,
it's just a game.

03:14.127 --> 03:15.095
Don't be so weird.

03:15.128 --> 03:16.163
Don't!

03:16.196 --> 03:17.197
Don't call me that.

03:17.231 --> 03:18.399
[ Inhales sharply ]

03:18.432 --> 03:20.668
Sorry.
Ah, it's okay.

03:20.701 --> 03:22.670
That stuff won't
mean a thing.

03:22.703 --> 03:25.273
I mean, that stuff don't
mean a thing.

03:25.306 --> 03:27.107
Hey, come on,
we're almost there!

03:27.140 --> 03:29.176
Whoop, whoop, whoop!

03:29.209 --> 03:30.678
Hey, wait up!

03:30.711 --> 03:32.346
Whoop, whoop!

03:32.380 --> 03:34.282
Whoop, whoop, whoop!

03:34.315 --> 03:36.784
Whoop, whoop, whoop!

03:36.817 --> 03:39.119
Whoop!
Whoop!

03:39.152 --> 03:41.289
Look, we're here!

03:41.322 --> 03:42.690
Where?

03:42.723 --> 03:45.125
I just see a bunch of rock,
swear to glob.

03:45.158 --> 03:47.060
But check this out.

03:47.094 --> 03:49.029
Whoa!
Magic key!

03:49.062 --> 03:51.432
I had to chop up
a bunch of stubborn so-and-so's

03:51.465 --> 03:54.201
to get my hands
on this baby.

03:54.234 --> 03:56.304
Dang!
You been busy.

04:02.743 --> 04:04.912
Wow, would you
look at that!

04:04.945 --> 04:08.215
They hid a ziggurat
in the cliff side.

04:08.248 --> 04:09.550
Amazing!

04:09.583 --> 04:12.052
Yeah, I poked around in there
a bit, but --

04:12.085 --> 04:14.121
Dut, dut, dut!
No spoilers!

04:14.154 --> 04:15.456
No, I know.

04:15.489 --> 04:16.824
I didn't go past
the first level.

04:16.857 --> 04:19.593
I was saving it
to do together.

04:19.627 --> 04:21.028
Sweet.

04:22.963 --> 04:25.165
Whoa, what is that,
a fitness pole?

04:25.198 --> 04:28.302
Hey ya, hey ya, hey ya!

04:28.336 --> 04:29.803
Come on.

04:33.441 --> 04:35.443
This way.

04:36.109 --> 04:38.779
Hey, Fern, wait up.

04:38.812 --> 04:41.349
Hey, I just want to say
that it's really cool

04:41.382 --> 04:42.650
that you're into
this stuff.

04:42.683 --> 04:45.018
You know -- that we have
so much in common.

04:45.052 --> 04:47.455
It feels almost like
we're real brothers, right?

04:47.488 --> 04:49.457
Or even closer.

04:53.126 --> 04:56.196
I think that's
the treasure chamber down there.

04:56.229 --> 04:58.098
Why don't you
go check it out?

04:58.131 --> 05:00.634
I want to study
these interesting carvings.

05:00.668 --> 05:01.935
Hmm.

05:01.969 --> 05:03.136
Fascinating.

05:03.170 --> 05:05.973
Oh.
Uh, okay.

05:06.006 --> 05:09.042
I guess just holler
if you need me.

05:12.212 --> 05:13.614
[ Sighs ]

05:13.647 --> 05:15.683
Hey, what's this?

05:15.716 --> 05:19.052
Contemporary chair,
contemporary trash,

05:19.086 --> 05:21.822
contemporary meatloaf.

05:21.855 --> 05:23.724
Hey, bad news, Fern.

05:23.757 --> 05:26.460
It looks like we've got
a squatter situation here.

05:26.494 --> 05:27.628
I think they got
the treasure,

05:27.661 --> 05:30.464
but they left
some meatloaf behind.

05:30.498 --> 05:33.667
The good news is I know
a meatloaf dealer--

05:33.701 --> 05:35.969
[ Muffled ]
What the?!

05:36.003 --> 05:37.538
Fern?

05:40.340 --> 05:41.709
Fern?

05:41.742 --> 05:43.076
[ Grunting ]

05:45.846 --> 05:47.080
Uh, Fern?

05:47.114 --> 05:49.650
I think maybe the wind
blew the door shut.

05:49.683 --> 05:52.152
An "act of nature,"
I would presume.

05:52.185 --> 05:55.589
I'm sorry. I don't actually
know how to make meatloaf.

05:55.623 --> 05:58.225
That's just
a pan of dirt.

05:58.258 --> 05:59.427
Well, that's okay.

05:59.460 --> 06:00.961
I don't know how to,
either!

06:04.632 --> 06:06.867
Fern, please
open the door.

06:10.137 --> 06:12.039
This is where you live now.

06:12.072 --> 06:14.074
You'll be fine.

06:14.107 --> 06:17.911
What?! Fern, what about Jake
and BMO -- my home?

06:17.945 --> 06:20.113
It's been your home
long enough.

06:20.147 --> 06:21.915
It's Fern's turn.

06:21.949 --> 06:24.885
I think I'm going to be
a really great Finn.

06:24.918 --> 06:27.521
Hey, do you know who
my favorite is?

06:27.555 --> 06:28.622
It's Neptr.

06:28.656 --> 06:31.525
I'm a Neptr guy!

06:31.559 --> 06:34.528
I'll be back in a month
with a new bucket of trash.

06:34.562 --> 06:35.996
Later!

06:38.566 --> 06:39.933
Fern!?

06:39.967 --> 06:41.602
[ Grunts ]

06:41.635 --> 06:44.404
I've been double-crossed
by grass Finn!

06:47.575 --> 06:50.043
I don't like being abandoned!

06:50.077 --> 06:52.112
I'm sensitive to it!

06:52.145 --> 06:53.714
[ Groans ]

06:53.747 --> 06:56.717
Mmm!

06:56.750 --> 07:01.254
[ Sighs ]
It's too hot!

07:01.288 --> 07:02.389
[ Groans ]

07:02.422 --> 07:03.724
[ Muttering ]

07:03.757 --> 07:06.159
There's got to be
something useful in here.

07:12.533 --> 07:14.101
[ Screams ]

07:14.134 --> 07:17.270
Oof!

07:17.304 --> 07:18.672
You'll be back in a month?

07:18.706 --> 07:20.974
With a new bucket of trash?

07:21.008 --> 07:23.276
It's hot!
There's no air in here!

07:23.310 --> 07:25.145
I need air!

07:25.178 --> 07:27.280
I need air!

07:27.314 --> 07:30.918
[ Whirring ]

07:30.951 --> 07:34.755
Wha?

07:34.788 --> 07:36.089
Oh!

07:36.123 --> 07:37.591
A microphone.

07:37.625 --> 07:39.159
There's some dried ketchup
on it.

07:42.229 --> 07:44.331
Uh, hello.

07:44.364 --> 07:46.934
[ Beeps ]

07:46.967 --> 07:48.135
Hi, Finn!

07:48.168 --> 07:51.104
You're still asleep
after your fight with Susan.

07:51.138 --> 07:53.440
But when you wake up,
I'm sure you'll have fun

07:53.473 --> 07:56.276
discovering everything
your new arm can do.

07:56.309 --> 07:58.478
And, Finn, sincerely,

07:58.512 --> 08:01.481
thank you for defending
our kingdom again.

08:01.515 --> 08:02.783
Oh.

08:02.816 --> 08:06.019
Someone else wants
to thank you, too.

08:06.053 --> 08:07.955
Thank you, Finn!

08:07.988 --> 08:08.956
[ Laughs ]

08:08.989 --> 08:10.057
I don't know.

08:10.090 --> 08:12.292
Okay, um...

08:12.325 --> 08:15.796
Welcome, Finn!

08:15.829 --> 08:17.164
Huh.

08:25.072 --> 08:26.607
Yes!

08:35.282 --> 08:37.184
[ Buzzing ]

08:37.217 --> 08:38.185
Huh?

08:38.218 --> 08:39.352
You donked up!

08:39.386 --> 08:41.488
[ Screams ]

08:41.521 --> 08:42.489
[ Brrrb! ]

08:42.522 --> 08:43.657
How did you get out?

08:43.691 --> 08:46.994
[ Grunts ]

08:47.027 --> 08:48.328
[ Growling ]

08:48.361 --> 08:50.998
Whoa!

08:51.031 --> 08:53.567
Hey!

08:53.601 --> 08:55.035
[ Grunting ]

08:58.038 --> 09:00.574
What do you think
you're doing?!

09:00.608 --> 09:02.042
I'm weed whacking.

09:02.075 --> 09:04.211
You've been Finn
long enough!

09:04.244 --> 09:06.013
It's my turn.

09:06.046 --> 09:07.347
[ Growls ]

09:07.380 --> 09:10.183
Fern, smarten up!

09:10.217 --> 09:12.385
Nuh-uh!

09:12.419 --> 09:13.687
What are you?

09:13.721 --> 09:15.589
A weed whacker!

09:15.623 --> 09:17.290
[ Hissing ]

09:20.393 --> 09:22.462
[ Grunting ]

09:22.495 --> 09:24.898
Nyuh!

09:28.068 --> 09:29.770
[ Hisses ]

09:34.107 --> 09:35.643
My belzer!

09:35.676 --> 09:37.878
[ Grunting ]

09:37.911 --> 09:40.580
Whoa!

09:40.614 --> 09:42.750
[ Panting ]

09:45.485 --> 09:46.887
[ Laughs ]

09:46.920 --> 09:49.389
Fern, if things
are going down the way

09:49.422 --> 09:50.891
I think they're going down --

09:50.924 --> 09:53.393
please tell Jake
I love him.

09:53.426 --> 09:54.628
That doesn't matter.

09:54.662 --> 09:56.229
I love him!

09:56.263 --> 09:57.397
I know you do, Fern.

09:57.430 --> 10:00.734
Listen, we can stop this
and just go home together.

10:00.768 --> 10:02.135
All this lying
and fighting,

10:02.169 --> 10:04.237
it doesn't have to end
like this.

10:04.271 --> 10:06.774
Today doesn't have to have
this kind of...

10:06.807 --> 10:08.475
finality.

10:08.508 --> 10:10.377
Fatality!

10:22.790 --> 10:23.757
[ Door opens ]

10:23.791 --> 10:26.593
[ Door closes ]

10:26.626 --> 10:27.761
Hey, boys!

10:27.795 --> 10:29.429
Y'all have fun
out there?

10:29.462 --> 10:31.331
Wait, what happened?

10:35.803 --> 10:37.470
I know that look.

10:37.504 --> 10:39.306
You just killed someone.

10:39.339 --> 10:41.074
[ Blows horn ]

10:49.482 --> 10:53.286
Almost done, champ.

10:53.320 --> 10:54.922
There you go.

10:59.359 --> 11:01.895
You looking for an uncle?

11:07.701 --> 11:11.638
♪ Come along with me

11:11.671 --> 11:16.209
♪ And the butterflies and bees

11:19.279 --> 11:21.949
This party is so crazy!
